Gakundu is a wet mill or “factory” located in Embu County on the eastern slopes of Mt. Kenya. Gakundu was established in  and together with  other co ee factories Kamviu, Gichugu and Gakui, it forms the Gakundu Farmers Coopertive Society. While this mill gathers  active members, the whole society has over  farmers registered. The mill is run by a factory manager but all activities are supervised by committee members. Gakundu, on average produces , kilos of green co ee annually consisting of cultivars SL and SL. The majority of the co ee processed through Gakundu comes from smallholder farmers who deliver ripe co ee cherries to the mill to be processed. The cherries are oated in water to sort for quality. Afterwards, the fruit is stripped mechanically before the seeds are fermented for  hours in open air. Next, the seeds are then moved to a tank with fresh water fro another  hours before being washed through canals to remove the remaining mucilage. Finally, the co ee is dried on raised beds in the sun. During the hottest parts of the day and coldest parts of the night, the co ee is covered in order to prevent extremes in drying conditions, promoting even drying.
