Hand labor represents about % of the production cost for coffee. Like many of the coffee pickers in Costa Rica, much of the labor are migrant workers from Nicaragua. About - pickers work at Jardin de Aromas from the middle of October through February. The same pickers come back every year, and Carole provides housing for them and their families.
