Dominated by tropical fruit notes and a blood orange acidity; Karogoto is a dynamic Nyeri county coffee reminiscent of a stone fruit nectar. 
The Tekangu Farmers Cooperative Society has been around for a mere  years. Known for being one of the premier cooperatives in all of Nyeri county, they receive coffee cherries from over , member smallholder farmers via their three factories; Tegu, Karogoto and Ngunguru. This lot is a selection of only the finest and ripest cherries delivered to the Karogoto factory. 
Once received, the coffee is pulped, soaked in water for  hours, cleaned, soaked again and then dried on raised beds. This process, known as "double fermentation", is unique to Kenya. Thanks to the characteristic second soaking, organic acids are said to more fully develop and the green coffee's moisture content is equalized to ensure more uniform drying.
The Karogoto factory has been prized for its steady stream of spectacular lots year to year and this year is no exception. Karogoto is located just outside of the town of Karatina in a region noted for having abundant and consistent rainfall patterns. This plus the backdrop of Mt. Kenya and the Aberdare mountain range provide for the perfect climate to grow exceptional coffee.
