			Its true, making really exceptional coffee takes time, commitment and training but that doesn’t mean it’s not possible for you to do at home. We take all our knowledge and experience, and share it with you in one of our three classes — Home Brewing, Espresso, and Steaming & Latte Art.
		

			Each class includes a good dose of theory while being very hands on, allowing you to really get the hang of everything we throw at you. We keep each gathering intimate so you get one-on-one time with our skilled barista teachers. Want to gift a class? We can do that too.
		
 Learning how to make amazing coffee at home can be intimidating, especially with so many tools, methods and information available. Our classes focus on making it simple for you. In the Home Brewing class we take you through a few of our favourite foolproof methods for home coffee brewing — French Press, Aeropress and pour-over. Armed with a bit of information, you leave our class feeling confident to make a great brewed coffee at home.
 Our Espresso and Steaming & Latte Art classes are meant to be taken one after the other. In our Espresso class, you’ll learn extraction and espresso techniques as you taste different varieties of espresso to understand what goes into making a great espresso.
 Our Espresso and Steaming & Latte Art classes are meant to be taken one after the other. In our Latte Art class, you’ll hone your milk steaming and pouring skills to enhance your espresso techniques. Plus, you’ll impress with your new found skills in latte art design.
So you’ve been to our cafes and maybe brewed our coffee at home. Now its time to go behind-the-scenes to our roasting operation and see where the magic happens. Okay, not so much magic as hard work. This -minute group session includes a guided tour of our roasterie as well as insight into our green coffee buying and a tasting. Once you’ve learned all about it, you get a bag of our coffee to take home.
With so many different coffee origins, varieties, roast styles and brewing methods, the world of coffee can seem completely confusing. In our Coffee Tastings we guide you through the different elements that create a fantastic coffee as you explore its subtle nuances for yourself.
